benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/admin/queues - Get queues entries

covered: Valid Request: Happy-path retrieval with and without filters, including combined filters (TC01–TC10).
Empty Response: Verified when no data exists and when filters exclude all data (TC11, TC29).

Query Parameters: Broad coverage of valid filters (accountId, queueName, serviceName, dates, booleans) and invalid inputs (invalid UUID, malformed dates), plus extra params tolerance (TC02–TC10, TC12–TC13, TC25).
Error Handling: 400, 404, 500, 503, 504 paths covered; error messaging consistency also considered (TC13–TC14, TC25, TC30, TC16, TC19, TC28).
Security/Injection: SQLi/XSS-style inputs tested and sanitized/blocked (TC17, TC26).
Concurrency: Simultaneous requests verified for correctness (TC20).
Performance/Large Data: Large dataset retrieval and response time threshold checked (TC18).
Defaults/Backward Compatibility: Booleans default to true; legacy behavior confirmed (TC01, TC22).
Flag Behavior: Explicit toggling of withHistory, withInProcessing, withBusEvents, withNotifications validated (TC06–TC09, TC21).
Content Type: application/octet-stream verified for success (TC01).
gaps: Pagination: No scenarios validate pagination behavior for large datasets (e.g., page/limit, next links, total counts).
Caching Behavior: No checks for ETag/Last-Modified, Cache-Control, or 304 responses with If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since.
Rate Limiting/Throttling: No tests for 429 or backoff headers under burst traffic.
RBAC/Forbidden: Only 401 covered; no 403 test for authenticated but unauthorized roles (if applicable to admin-only endpoint).
Streaming/Download Semantics: No verification of content-disposition, chunked transfer, or integrity of the octet-stream format/schema.
Date Edge Cases: No test for minDate > maxDate, timezone/UTC handling, or inclusive/exclusive boundary behavior.
Content Negotiation: No tests around Accept header variations or incorrect Accept leading to 406 (if supported).
Observability Headers: No verification of correlation/request IDs or standard error schema shape in actual responses (TC28 is high-level only).
recommendations: Add pagination scenarios: page/limit parameters, boundary pages, total count, empty last page, and large dataset paging correctness.
Introduce caching tests: validate ETag/Last-Modified on first response, repeat with If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since expecting 304; verify Cache-Control policies.
Add rate limiting tests: send bursts to trigger 429, verify Retry-After/backoff behavior and that non-throttled requests still succeed.
Include RBAC tests: authenticated non-admin user gets 403 (if endpoint is admin-only).
Verify streaming/download specifics: check Content-Disposition (if file-like), chunked transfer, and validate parsed content structure of the octet-stream for correctness.
Expand date validation: minDate > maxDate returns 400; test timezone offsets (Z, +/-hh:mm) and boundary inclusivity (entries exactly at min/max).
Test Accept header handling: correct response for application/octet-stream; invalid/unsupported Accept returns 406 (if applicable).
Strengthen error schema checks: assert concrete fields (code, message, type, requestId), and traceability headers (X-Request-Id/Correlation-Id) across error paths.
